&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: 0pt TEXT-INDENT: -0.25in; 0.25in; .25in? l0 lfo1; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list&gt;&lt;SPAN Ignore? **Zowie**?mso-list:&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN Ignore? **Zowie**?mso-list:&gt;1.&amp;nbsp; Move the Twisted Chance discipline&amp;nbsp;to the Deadeye&amp;nbsp;discipline&amp;nbsp;timer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" &gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;-&amp;nbsp;Twisted Chance(lvl 65)&amp;nbsp;is on the same timer as Duelist(lvl 59), and&amp;nbsp;the "supposed" upgrade to Duelist.&amp;nbsp; While TC will outperform Duelist in certain situations, they are extremely rare. &amp;nbsp;Duelist is still used over Twisted Chance by the &lt;STRONG&gt;vast&lt;/STRONG&gt; majority of the rogues.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2. Nerves of Steel AA is not working as intended. &lt;SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(Rashere is looking into fixing the description on this AA.&amp;nbsp; QA is looking into sneak/hide being broken after a successful resist.)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- Sneak/Hide is being broken even after a successful resist of an AE.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Additonally many rogues would like to see a change to the description of the AA so that its intended effect is more clear.&amp;nbsp; Specifically the details concerning single target spells.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3. Implement&amp;nbsp;a form of&amp;nbsp;minor endurance preservation foci, or an&amp;nbsp;endurance preservation&amp;nbsp;foci that specificly effects the Assassin strike line of disciplines.&amp;nbsp; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;- Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- This issue is closely related to issue #4, and therefore could be combined in to one issue.&amp;nbsp; Your discretion.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; **Zowie**?MARGIN: TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN Ignore? **Zowie**?mso-list:&gt;&lt;SPAN Roman?? ?Times New 7pt **Zowie**?FONT:&gt;4.&lt;FONT color=#000000&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;Minimum bs damage should scale with weapon / Scale Chaotic Stab with weapon damage &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:&gt;(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; **Zowie**?MARGIN: TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; **Zowie**?MARGIN: TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; **Zowie**?MARGIN: TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; **Zowie**?MARGIN: TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;5. &amp;nbsp;Slightly increase the availability of tradable and single group weapons that allow more casual, unguilded, and/or non raiding rogues to stay relatively viable.&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman" color=#ff0000 size=3&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:&gt;(currently being evaluated)&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt; &lt;FONT color=#0033cc&gt;*Reworded*&lt;/FONT&gt; &#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; **Zowie**?MARGIN: TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; **Zowie**?MARGIN: TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;6. &amp;nbsp; Assassin’s Strike is still not effective enough for the endurance cost,&amp;nbsp; should be effective on double and triple bs if used when these work and damage cap made higher &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;FONT size=3&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman"&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:&gt;(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; **Zowie**?MARGIN: TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt; **Zowie**?MARGIN: TEXT-ALIGN: justify?&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;7.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;Shroud of Stealth should make it so monsters see a rogue much more rarely then it does &lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman" color=#ff0000 size=3&gt;(currently being evaluated) - Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;SPAN FONT-FAMILY: COLOR: 9pt; Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-SIZE: silver;&gt;&lt;o:p&gt;&lt;/o:p&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp; 8. Poisons&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt; (no change planned at this time)&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0000ff&gt; - perhaps a revision for the future on this &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;- Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Integrate all old world poisons into the PoP poison system (including the ability to make 10 dose vials with&amp;nbsp;the 10-15 min durations) &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Make poisons more viable by modifying the resist checks so they aren't so easily resisted. &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Add new, interesting, and more powerful &amp;nbsp;poison recipes.&amp;nbsp; Extremely powerful, but extremely rare poisons would be a nice addition. &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Add an upgrade to the poison mastery AA that would allow increased durations, effectiveness, and the ability to poison others weapons. &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Reduce the time investment required to collect components for lesser or more common poisons. Possibly through a better yield in combines or more components being made purchasable. &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Add the ability to poison thrown weapons.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/STRONG&gt;9.&amp;nbsp; Traps&amp;nbsp;and lockpicking &lt;FONT color=#0000ff&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;(no change planned at this time)&lt;/FONT&gt; - perhaps a revision for the future on this &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;- Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Add &amp;nbsp;the ability to permanently, or at least greatly increase the time that a trap stays disarmed after a successful attempt.&amp;nbsp; This is the most tedious and irritating thing about traps.&amp;nbsp; It's no fun to have to stand in the same place spamming a key to keep a trap disarmed.&amp;nbsp; This would be a great AA. &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Add the ability to "see" traps via a target ring.&amp;nbsp; Perfect idea for an AA. &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Add the ability to "mark" traps&amp;nbsp;(once identified by a rogue) for others to see. Rogue specific or possibly raid/group leader AA. &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Make traps/locks have more of an impact in some (don't over do it ! =P)&amp;nbsp;raid and group situations.&amp;nbsp; If traps&amp;nbsp;could be seen, and/or marked by a rogue, making them a lot more unforgiving would add an element of danger that a skilled rogue could take pride in overcoming. &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Add the ability to "set" traps after obtaining the highest level of trap AA (this would add signifcant&amp;nbsp;value to an aa that is currently considered useless).&amp;nbsp; Snare, DD's, root, dispel, etc.&amp;nbsp; It could require tradeskill components (such as tinkering, smithing , or tailoring) to increase the usefulness of said tradeskills and help with balance. &#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Allow rogues to identify/disarm ALL traps and pick any lock&amp;nbsp;in LDoN.&amp;nbsp; Rogues are the masters of these two abilities, not to mention they are class defining skills.&amp;nbsp; Sharing the abilities with other classes isn't an issue, but reducing the effectiveness of our own makes absolutely no sense. &lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; 10. Improved corpse dragging.&amp;nbsp;&lt;SPAN red? **Zowie**?COLOR:&gt;&lt;FONT face="Times New Roman" color=#ff0000 size=3&gt;(currently being evaluated)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/SPAN&gt; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;- Most likely this will be considered as part of the class re-envisioning&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; This could be implemented through several means:&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; - Pre-consent&amp;nbsp; - Allow players to tag other players with the ability to drag their corpse before death.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; - Raid consent -&amp;nbsp; Allow raid leaders to designate a set number of individuals with the ability to drag any corpse(indefinitely) within the raid.&amp;nbsp; &lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; - Increase the number of corpses that can be drug at once.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;BUG: Fix the interaction (bug)&amp;nbsp;between sneak/hide and Bard invis.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;- This bug is not always specific to Bard songs. Some rogues have experienced the breaking of hide when a cast invis spell fades.&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
